The paper discusses a new deep learning autoencoder network that learns features that show part-based representation of data. This topic is closely related to machine learning and computer vision, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.LG and cs.CV. The paper also mentions the use of nonnegativity constraints, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks and optimization algorithms, suggesting that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.NE and cs.AI. Finally, the paper tests its algorithm on image and text data sets, indicating that it could also be relevant to the sub-category cs.CL, which covers natural language processing and computational linguistics.
